What is a "Job"?
When a user submits a complex analysis request, the system creates a Job — a unit of work with a unique ID (job_id). Each job gets its own folder to store input data, intermediate outputs, and the final HTML report.

What is a "Session"?
A Session represents a user's working context — all the data files they uploaded and all the jobs they ran belong to one session. Multiple jobs can belong to one session.

What are "Tokens"?
AI language models (like GPT-4) charge by the number of "tokens" (roughly words/word-pieces) they process. This system tracks tokens consumed and calculates the monetary cost.

