Each stage waits for the previous one to fully complete before starting. There is no concurrent execution between agents. EDA cannot run while hypothesis is already being planned, etc.

3. EDA Tasks Also Run Sequentially Inside EDA Agent
Inside EDAAgent, the 5 tasks per cycle run one at a time through execute_task() — each involving an LLM call, then Jupyter execution, then waiting for the output. There is no asyncio.gather() across the 5 tasks.

4. Jupyter Kernel Cold Start
class JupyterExecutionTool:
    def __init__(self):
        self.km = KernelManager()
        self.km.start_kernel()     # ← Cold start every time
        self.kc = self.km.client()
        self.kc.start_channels()
        self._setup_kernel()       # ← Runs setup code (imports, patches)
Starting a Jupyter kernel and loading pandas, numpy, matplotlib, seaborn takes 5–15 seconds. This happens at least once per agent (EDA, Hypothesis, and Narrator each lazily create their own CodeAgent). The comment in the code even calls this out:

